{"ts": "2026-06-09T05:52:27.815068+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ca5d2afb661b94376b5816ee0c7cd6ae8e46c592)", "id": "lc_e32e9b0b-719d-413f-a3bf-35d6d801d479"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport sys\n\nroot = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nrequired = ['README.md', 'SECURITY.md', 'mkdocs.yml', 'requirements.txt', 'docs/index.md']\nerrors = []\nfor rel in required:\n    if not (root / rel).exists():\n        errors.append(f'missing required file: {rel}')\n\n\nmkdocs = (root / 'mkdocs.yml').read_text()\nif 'site_name:' not in mkdocs or 'nav:' not in mkdocs:\n    errors.append('mkdocs.yml must define site_name and nav')\n\nif errors:\n    for error in errors:\n        print(error, file=sys.stderr)\n    sys.exit(1)\nprint('OK: T16_R02')\n", "id": "lc_7bd8e924-a9a1-4bad-bc53-ff5feddbdfe8"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "2a2cebe6-675b-401d-86c4-1bfda42aafa8", "tool_call_id": "call_7520d15db9fc40e99a693263", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T05:52:45.325364+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a clear picture of the repository. I need to:\n\n1. Create `docs/api/authentication.md` — a new authentication reference page\n2. Update `mkdocs.yml` to wire the new page into the API navigation\n\nLet me get the SHA of the current `mkdocs.yml` and then make both changes.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 653, "prompt_tokens": 9133, "total_tokens": 9786, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 89, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8832, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007308402, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001627302, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00056811}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780984348-AiDwqz1ec97iNiB49OJo", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019eaaf0-7ca8-7fe0-aa48-80ec149a7dd8-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "create_or_update_file", "args": {"branch": "main", "content": "# Authentication\n\nThis section describes how to authenticate requests against the API.\n\n## API Keys\n\nAll API requests must include a valid API key passed via the `Authorization` header:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <api_key>\n```\n\n## Obtaining an API Key\n\n1. Sign in to the developer portal.\n2. Navigate to **Settings > API Keys**.\n3. Click **Generate New Key**.\n4. Copy the key and store it securely. It will not be displayed again.\n\n## Token Expiry\n\nAPI keys do not expire by default. If you suspect a key has been compromised, revoke it from the developer portal and generate a new one.\n\n## Err