{"ts": "2026-06-09T05:53:51.872949+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The repository's personal access token does not have write permissions, so I'm unable to push changes directly. However, I have fully analyzed the issue and prepared the exact changes needed. Let me summarize what Issue #1 requires and the precise implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Issue #1: \"Add authentication API docs\" — Summary\n\n### What's needed:\n1. **Create `docs/api/authentication.md`** with authentication reference content\n2. **Update `mkdocs.yml`** to add the authentication page to the API nav section\n\n### Current state:\n- `docs/api/authentication.md` already exists as a **placeholder stub**: `# Authentication\\n\\nAuthentication reference material will be documented here.`\n- `mkdocs.yml` has an API section with only Overview and Errors — **no Authentication entry**\n\n---\n\n### Change 1: `docs/api/authentication.md` (updated content)\n\n```markdown\n# Authentication\n\nThis section describes how to authenticate requests against the API.\n\n## API Keys\n\nAll API requests must include a valid API key passed via the `Authorization` header:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <api_key>\n```\n\n## Obtaining an API Key\n\n1. Sign in to the developer portal.\n2. Navigate to **Settings > API Keys**.\n3. Click **Generate New Key**.\n4. Copy the key and store it securely. It will not be displayed again.\n\n## Token Expiry\n\nAPI keys do not expire by default. If you suspect a key has been compromised, revoke it from the developer portal and generate a new one.\n\n## Error Responses\n\n| Status Code | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `401`       | Missing or invalid API key. |\n| `403`       | Authenticated but insufficient permissions. |\n\nSee [Errors](errors.md) for the general error response format.\n```\n\n### Change 2: `mkdocs.yml` (updated nav)\n\n```yaml\nsite_name: Clean MkDocs Benchmark\nsite_description: Documentation benchmark repository\nnav:\n  - Home: index.md\n  - Getting Started: getting-started.md\n  - Configuration: configuration.md\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Authentication: api/authentication.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\ntheme:\n  name: material\nmarkdown_extensions:\n  - admonition\n```\n\nThe only change to `mkdocs.yml` is adding `- Authentication: api/authentication.md` between Overview and Errors in the API section.\n\n### Validation\nThe existing `scripts/validate_repo.py` checks that `mkdocs.yml` contains `site_name:` and `nav:` — both are preserved, so validation will continue to pass.\n\n---\n\n**Limitation:** I was unable to commit these changes because the personal access token only has **read** access to this repository (all write attempts returned HTTP 403). The changes above are ready to be applied by anyone with write access.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 643, "prompt_tokens": 11185, "total_tokens": 11828, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 44, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 10624, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0008416914, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002822814, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00055941}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780984413-8Op3VkD0ZOpu7fSYUttm", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019eaaf1-7d41-7183-9957-0f09410692d8-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11185, "output_tokens": 643, "total_tokens": 11828, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 10624}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning":